
# RugRoom Installation Guide

Requirements
------------
- Windows 10/11 64-bit
- Internet connection
- VR headset (optional):
  - Meta Quest via Link/Air Link
  - SteamVR headset


Downloading RugRoom
-------------------
Download the RugRoom client package.

The folder should contain:

RugRoom/
|
|-- BepInEx/
|-- RecRoom_Data/
|-- recroom.exe
|-- RecRoomScreen.bat
|-- RecRoomVR.bat
|-- download.bat

Do not move files out of this folder.


Installing the Client
---------------------
Run:

download.bat

This will:
- Download required game files
- Install BepInEx
- Prepare the client

Wait until it fully completes.


Launching RugRoom
-----------------

Desktop Mode:
Run:

RecRoomScreen.bat


VR Mode:
1. Connect your headset to your PC.
2. Start SteamVR or Oculus Link/Air Link.
3. Run:

RecRoomVR.bat


Account Creation
----------------
When RugRoom opens:

1. Select Create Account.
2. Enter your information.
3. Finish registration.
4. Log in.


Troubleshooting
---------------

Stuck on Creating Account:
- Check BepInEx/LogOutput.log
- Make sure the server is online.

VR Does Not Start:
- Make sure SteamVR is running.
- Make sure your headset is connected.
- Use RecRoomVR.bat.

Game Closes Immediately:
- Check BepInEx/LogOutput.log for errors.


Updating RugRoom
----------------
1. Close RugRoom.
2. Replace the client files with the newest version provided in the discord. 
3. Run download.bat if required.


Controls
--------

Desktop:
- WASD: Move
- Mouse: Look
- Space: Jump

VR:
- Left controller: Movement
- Right controller: Look and interaction


